author: Danny Segura
title: Khalil Rountree knocks out Daniel Jolly with vicious knee to the head at UFC Fight Night 104
text: — UFC Canada (@UFC_CA) February 5, 2017 Khalil Rountree picked up his first win inside the octagon, and he did in brutal fashion. The former Ultimate Fighter 23 cast member knocked out Daniel Jolly in less than a minute into their fight at Saturday’s UFC Fight Night 104 in Houston. With this performance, Rountree snapped a two-fight losing streak that began in his UFC career. The 26-year-old light heavyweight is now 5-2 as a professional fighter, and 1-2 in the UFC.
